    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-16T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-16T11:00:00-05:00" n="719"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.516/138: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-16T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 16, 1920—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. My 37, June 12, 9 a.m. From McIlhenny:</p>
                <p>Since my cable, attitude of Haitian Government has changed. Now refuses to accept
                    modifications of charter.<note n="62" xml:id="d719fn62">See letter of the
                        Financial Adviser of Haiti to the Chief of the Division of Latin American
                        Affairs, Department of State, July 21, <ref target="#pg_762">p.
                        762</ref>.</note> For this and other reasons I have temporarily suspended
                    discussion of budget.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
